createRuler(25.10)                                          createRuler(25.10)

Name
       createRuler - Adds a ruler

Syntax
       createRuler

       [-help]

       {{-center {<x y>} -radius <value>} | -coordinates {<x1 y1 x2 y2> ...}}

       Adds  a  ruler.  For  an  orthogonal ruler, use -coordinates to specify
       ruler segments. For a circular ruler, use -center and -radius.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each createRuler parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man createRuler

       -center {<x y>}
              Specifies the coordinates for the center of a circular ruler.

       -coordinates {<x1 y1 x2 y2 ...>}
              Specifies the beginning and ending  coordinates  for  the  ruler
              line segments. The values are in microns.

       -radius <value>
              Specifies  the  radius of a circular ruler. The value is of type
              float.

Example
              * The following command creates a circular ruler of  radius  500
                with the center at {0 0}:

                createRuler -center {0 0} -radius 500

